1
00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:06,830
In this video we are going to learn microservices, synchronous communication and best practices.

2
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:13,310
As we said before, in synchronous communication, the client sends a request with using Http protocols

3
00:00:13,310 --> 00:00:15,740
and waits for a response from the service.

4
00:00:16,070 --> 00:00:21,470
So the synchronous communication protocols can be mainly Http or Https.

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:28,490
You can also see the image that represents Microsoft Sync communication client application called microservices

6
00:00:28,490 --> 00:00:29,720
and microservices.

7
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:36,380
Return response by visiting several internal microservices using the Http and gRPC protocol.

8
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:43,830
For synchronous communication, we understood that we should follow request response communication model

9
00:00:43,830 --> 00:00:49,050
with Http and Rest protocols, and we can extend this gRPC and GraphQL.

10
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:54,120
So under these synchronous communication model we can also divide by four.

11
00:00:54,150 --> 00:01:00,570
The first one is Rest Http APIs when exposing from microservices.

12
00:01:00,570 --> 00:01:05,580
The second one is gRPC APIs when communicate internal microservices.

13
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:12,990
The third one is GraphQL API when structured flexible data in microservices, and the last one is WebSocket

14
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:16,320
APIs when real time bidirectional communication.

